One man is dead and two others were injured after a shooting at Durban s Glebelands Hostel.The latest shooting on Wednesday night brings the number of people who have died to nearly 80 in the hostel precinct in less than two years. Details of the latest incident are still sketchy but SAPS spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed that a man was killed and two others were injured.The attack comes in the same week that Public Protector investigators were due to visit Glebelands which has earned the unwanted moniker of the hostel of death . 